<plot>The program is an episode in a series titled The Eleventh Hour that appeared on Channel 4. It includes screenings of Noel Burch's film 'The Year of the Bodyguard' and Lezli-An Barrett's film 'An Epic Poem', both about suffragettes, followed by a discussion between critic Pam Cook and independent filmmakers Noel Burch and Lezli-an Barrett about gender issues in film history.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?555108</url></doc>
